<br>
It is not always best to use your pet against your opponent,  the pet will unmez the target every time so against like wizards or druids i never like to use them.  Basically in this type combat you mez nuke mez again pretty effective and pretty straightforward.  A nice thing to do during the mezzed period is to cast rune on yourself to always leave a buffer between you and the next incoming nuke. Gives you a couple few hundred HP wall before you sustain damage and can be very very effective when giving up many levels to a higher caster.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uzarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarius</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://media.xoom.com/website/animated-gifs/design-sets/electric/etc/elcmisc3.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guild Leader</span><br>  Posts: 411<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/00 1:31:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://media.xoom.com/website/animated-gifs/design-sets/electric/etc/elcmisc3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duelling as enchanter </span><hr size=1> Another advantage of the enchanter and the mez nuke mez technique is that while your opponent is mezz'd you can  get a few prescious moments of mana regeneration if its coming down to the wire. Mes..sit and med while rune is in effect you will have that buffer adnyou can mez rune nuke mez and do it all over again.<br>
<br>
<br>
I dont see any reason you should lose a duel as an enchanter unless your opponent has some serious magic resistances. <br>
